          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The integrated beam fluence was 1.49x10**18 ions",
                "delivered over a period of 41 days. (58% of this time",
                "was spent taking data for the 59Co+209Bi reaction.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Each set of nine 1.4x9 cm sector targets, nominally",
                "500 microg/cm2 Bi metal evaporated onto 150-300",
                "microg/cm2 Al substrates, was mounted on a 30-cm",
                "diameter swiftly rotating wheel."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The focal plane detector system was a linear",
                "array of five adjacent Si wafers, with each wafer",
                "having ten detector strips on it that were 3-mm wide",
                "and 28-mm high. Each detector strip was",
                "position-sensitive in the 28-mm direction. The",
                "depletion depth of the detectors was 100 microm and",
                "the average implantation depth of a compound nucleus",
                "recoil was 8 microm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASPEC",
                "EDE",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam entered the separator",
                "through a thin window (50-250 microg/cm2 of C or C-A1-",
                "C). The beam then struck the 0.5 mg/cm2 Bi metal",
                "targets which were mounted on a rapidly rotating",
                "target wheel to dissipate the energy deposited by the",
                "beam. The signals from the dE/dx detector (which was",
                "in front of the focal plane array) were used to",
                "identify recoil implantation and fission events, and",
                "by their absence, alpha-particle events."
              ]
            }
          ],
